{{wiktionary}}

'''Alphons''' is a male given name, originally from a [[Germanic name|Germanic]] ''Adalfuns'', composed of the elements ''adal'' "noble" and ''funs'' "eager, brave, ready".

Variants of the name include: '''''Alfonso''''' (Italian and Spanish), '''''Alfons''''' ([[Catalan language|Catalan]], Dutch, German, Polish and Scandinavian), '''''Afonso''''' ([[Portuguese language|Portuguese]] and [[Galician language|Galician]]), '''''Affonso''''' (Ancient Portuguese), '''''[[Alphonse]]''''', '''''Alfonse''''' (Italian, French and English), '''''Αλφόνσος''''' ''Alphonsos'' (Greek), '''''Alphonsus''''' (Latin), '''''Alphons''''' (Dutch), '''''Alfonsu''''' in ([[Leonese language|Leonese]]), '''''Alfonsas''''' (Lithuanian).<ref>http://www.ohbabynames.com/meaning/name/alfonso/1833</ref>

